 of companies whose stocks are held in client portfolios our approach generates a portfolio of stocks that on average usually have the following characteristics compared to the standard and poors  and russell top  indices higher historic earnings growth as measured by yearearningspershare growth rates provide a comparable level of dividend yield are more profitable than the aggregate sp  index as measured by return on equity a lower priceearnings ratio   welcome  midwest family wealth management midwest family wealth management  n liberty st morris il  phone  toll free  fax  jerrymidwestfamilywealthcom quick links contact us become a client calculators market summary companywelcomecompanyour teamproducts  serviceslinksabout lpl financialour approachclient centeraccount accessbecome a clientseminar registrationoptinget a quoteannuity quotedisability insurance quotegroup health insurance quote individual health insurance quotelife insurance quotelongterm care quotesecond to die life quote tax centertax calendartax forms librarytax organizertax publicationsinformationbook reviewbusiness ownerstaxed by selfemployment plans helping employees save for educationa growing trend  women entrepreneurscharitable givingcharitable giving and tax benefitscharitable planning donor advised funds vs private foundationscomplexity reigns when claiming a charitable deductioneconomics economic forecasts understanding the basicsunderstanding interest rates and your financial situationunderstanding the consumer price indexeducation planning plans a college savings alternativea savings plan that pays for more than just collegeapplying for federal aid for collegeweekly market commentaryweekly market commentarypersonal financetis the seasonto control holiday spendingretirementsocial security and retirement what you need to know researchmarket summaryquotesportfoliosmutual fundsindustry newssectorscalculatorscontact uscontact us tell a friendrequest infolocate us welcome to midwest family weal